<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFFDFFD9FF8DFA9BFD66FDA3" lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="315" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFFDFFD6FF8DFA9BFE3BF984" blockId="39.[113,1089,1405,1588]" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FF8DFA9BFF5EFA24" bold="true" box="[113,224,1405,1428]" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFDFFD6FF1BFA9BFEC3FA24" author="SPAETH" box="[231,381,1405,1428]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">SPAETH (1911)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FE02FA9BFD3DFA24" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[510,643,1405,1428]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FE02FA9BFD3DFA24" box="[510,643,1405,1428]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">C. speculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FD5AFA9BFD48FA24" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[678,758,1405,1428]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FD5AFA9BFD48FA24" box="[678,758,1405,1428]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">Orexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but noted that it was unknown to him. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FF3FFA7BFE3EFA04" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[195,384,1437,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FF3FFA7BFE3EFA04" box="[195,384,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">Orexita speculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was so far known only from a single and partially scletotized specimen. It is characterised by coarse and sparse punctation of elytra extending on explanate margin and colouration very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FDE3FA3BFCCBFA44" authority="(Champion, 1894)" baseAuthorityName="Champion" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[543,885,1501,1524]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripartita">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FDE3FA3BFD1DFA44" box="[543,675,1501,1524]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. tripartita</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFDFFD6FD4FFA3BFCD3FA44" author="Champion" box="[691,877,1501,1524]" firstAuthor="Champion" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" refId="ref49037" refString="CHAMPION G. C. 1894: [Cassidae]. Pp. 165 - 232. In: GODMAN F. D. &amp; SALVIN O. (eds): Biologia Centrali- Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. VI. Part 2. Phytophaga (part). Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 249 pp. + 13 pls." type="book" year="1894">Champion, 1894</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, it has a stouter body like 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFDFFD6FED3FA1BFE73F9A4" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[303,461,1533,1556]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagipennis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFDFFD6FED3FA1BFE73F9A4" box="[303,461,1533,1556]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="314">O. plagipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in my opinion it is conspecific with the latter as both differ only in colouration.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFF2FFD9FF49FF3AFD66FDA3" blockId="40.[151,1127,220,595]" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFF2FFD9FF49FF3AFEF5FF43" author="SPAETH" box="[181,331,220,243]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">SPAETH (1911)</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FE3FFF3AFDE1FF43" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[451,607,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagipennis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FE3FFF3AFDE1FF43" box="[451,607,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. plagipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closest to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FD1AFF3AFCE3FF43" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[742,861,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FD1AFF3AFCE3FF43" box="[742,861,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in 1) colouration as it is mostly black with yellow anterior margin of pronotum and red oval spot situated around midlength of explanate margin of each elytron; 2) significantly larger size; 3) less rounded anterior margin of the pronotum; 4) smaller and not fully rectangular basal corners of the pronotum; and 5) broader, in proportion to its width shorter pronotum. All these characters, except of the colouration, are identical to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FD64FE9AFCA3FE23" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[664,797,380,403]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FD64FE9AFCA3FE23" box="[664,797,380,403]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. speculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and hence I synonymize it with the latter species. On the other hand the differences between 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FCE2FE7AFC05FE03" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[798,955,412,435]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagipennis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FCE2FE7AFC05FE03" box="[798,955,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. plagipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FC13FE7AFBD8FE03" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[1007,1126,412,435]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FC13FE7AFBD8FE03" box="[1007,1126,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are rather minor and might easily be subject to intraspecific variability. However, I retain 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FF6BFE3AFEAAFE43" box="[151,276,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FF6BFE3AFEAAFE43" box="[151,276,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FEC5FE3AFE6BFE43" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[313,469,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagipennis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FEC5FE3AFE6BFE43" box="[313,469,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. plagipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as a valid taxon until I obtain more material for comparative purposes. See additional comments under 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFF2FFD9FDA5FE1AFD6FFDA3" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[601,721,508,531]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFF2FFD9FDA5FE1AFD6FFDA3" box="[601,721,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="315">O. wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
